Governor Ben Ayade of Cross River State has rescheduled the take off date for the no mask no movement order to Monday, April 6, 2020. Ayade who spoke through his Special Adviser Media and Publicity, Mr. Christian Ita stated that the policy is geared towards shielding the from the ravaging coronavirus pandemic. “The order which was to take effect from midnight Thursday, 2nd April 2020 will now commence on Moday, 6th April, 2020.” Ayade stressed. The Governor averred that the shift is necessitated by the need to allow the Garment Factory enough time to produce more masks for further free deliveries to the people and residents of Cross River state. He said that the change of date is to ensure that more people have the masks before enforcement commences. According to the state Governor, “Cross River Under my watch is committed to ensuring that the COVID-19 pandemic does not gain a foothold in the state”. The Governor stressed that spite the change of date for enforcement of no nose mask no movement”, the order banning movements into the state remains in force stressing that all entry points remain shut. He said that individuals wishing to leave state can do so adding that, no one is allowed into the state at this time.